{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"192111a0-0126-41fe-ac90-7e47111265ac","content":"For a .NET 8 CPU issue, **`dotnet-trace`** is the easiest option:\n\n```powershell\n# Install (one-time)\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-trace\n\n# Find your process ID\ndotnet-trace ps\n\n# Collect a 30-second CPU trace\ndotnet-trace collect -p <PID> --profile cpu-sampling --duration 00:00:30\n```\n\nThis produces a `.nettrace` file you can open in **Visual Studio** (Diagnostics Hub) or **PerfView**.\n\n### If you need deeper OS-level data, use **PerfView** instead:\n```powershell\n# Download from https://github.com/microsoft/perfview/releases\nPerfView.exe collect /CircularMB:500 /BufferSizeMB:256 /ThreadTime\n# Reproduce the issue, then click \"Stop Collection\"\n```\n\n**Quick guidance:**\n\n| Tool | Best for | Admin needed? |\n|---|---|---|\n| `dotnet-trace` | Managed-code hot paths | No |\n| PerfView | Full ETW (CPU, GC, I/O, waits) | Yes |\n\nSince you have admin and the CPU is pegged, start with `dotnet-trace` for a quick look. If the hot path is in native code or you need GC/contention data, switch to PerfView.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"965a4465-2420-4931-97b5-e18fe4e029d9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about collecting a CPU trace for a .NET 8 service on Windows Server. This is a knowledge/advice question, not a code task. I should give a concise, practical answer.\n\nThe best tool for this scenario is `dotnet-trace` or PerfView. For CPU profiling specifically, `dotnet-trace` is the simplest, but PerfView gives richer ETW-based CPU sampling data. Since they have admin access and want CPU trace specifically, I'd recommend `dotnet-trace` for simplicity or PerfView for deeper analysis.\n\nActually, for CPU specifically, `dotnet-trace` with the `cpu-sampling` profile is the easiest. PerfView is more powerful but heavier. \n\nI'll keep my answer straightforward and actionable.","outputTokens":513,"requestId":"6087:2A1B2F:219465:2B94C7:69FFDF32"},"id":"3123712f-eadc-4d4c-9312-2cff31ed6936","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:28:31.904Z","parentId":"2e737a32-9ad3-4ab0-b3ae-2eba8a87c53b"}
